## Shared UX Principles (All Surfaces)

- **Design system anchored to Figma.** Do not introduce UI component libraries that conflict with the established Figma design system. All new components are designed in Figma first.
- **Responsive always.** All screens must be tested at mobile viewport sizes. Do not ship UI that breaks on mobile, even for desktop-primary surfaces.
- **Accessibility.** Color alone cannot convey status. Use iconography and text together. WCAG AA compliance is the baseline.
- **Agentic over analytical.** Across all surfaces, features that enable action are higher priority than features that only display information.
